    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) serving as the clear anchors of the offensive engine. **Kyle Tucker** benefits tremendously from a premium matchup against Jose Quintana, with favorable park factors adding 14% to his base projection. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** finds himself in a high-leverage spot against Seth Lugo; despite a slight discount for Lugo\u2019s elite ability to hold baserunners, the combination of an aggressive #2 order slot and favorable wind conditions makes **Gunnar Henderson** a must-start. **Andy Pages** (74.43) also garners significant value in that same high-upside environment, rounding out a potent top tier for our daily lineup.\n\nThe optimizer faced a difficult choice regarding the bench, ultimately leaving **Coby Mayo** (50.81) on the sidelines in favor of **Brady House** (60.72) at 3B. While **Coby Mayo** has shown flashes of power, he was penalized by a negative platoon adjustment and a lower-tier batting order projection compared to **Brady House**, whose 9% platoon boost against Bryce Elder proved decisive. Meanwhile, we remain in a holding pattern with **Jackson Merrill** and **Luis Robert Jr.**, both of whom are ineligible today due to team off-days, depriving us of their critical stolen base potential. We continue to monitor the status of **Drake Baldwin**, **Liam Hicks**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Josh Lowe** to ensure those \"Lineup Pending\" designations don't result in unfavorable pinch-hit scenarios or defensive replacements that could impact our efficiency.",
